    • CompoundFilter

      public CompoundFilter​(CFType filterType, boolean checkMidLoop, boolean onEmptyResult, List<Predicate<T>> filterList)

      The fully parameterized CompoundFilter constructor; all other constructors must either directly or indirectly use this constructor.

      Parameters:
      filterType - The CFType enum defining how this CompoundFilter compares its Sub-Filters. If the specified value is null, the CFType defaults to CFType.ANY.
      checkMidLoop - Tells this CompoundFilter whether it should check if it can deduce a guaranteed return value after each individual Sub-Filter is called.
      onEmptyResult - Tells this CompoundFilter what result should be returned if this CompoundFilter has no Sub-Filters added.
      filterList - The list of Sub-Filters to be called by this CompoundFilter given the aforementioned CFType.
